00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:20.230 align:middle line:84%
which means that--
now, we can go--

00:18:20.230 --> 00:18:23.580 align:middle line:84%
of course there's been a lot
of speculation and discussion.

00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:28.950 align:middle line:84%
Somebody said that-- that
when the Twin Towers were

00:18:28.950 --> 00:18:32.050 align:middle line:84%
collapsing, and we're
talking about 350,000

00:18:32.050 --> 00:18:36.710 align:middle line:90%
tons of concrete and steel.

00:18:36.710 --> 00:18:39.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is like
a little earthquake.

00:18:39.830 --> 00:18:43.230 align:middle line:84%
It would be no surprise, say,
if the foundation of Building

00:18:43.230 --> 00:18:45.560 align:middle line:90%
Seven had been damaged, OK?

00:18:45.560 --> 00:18:48.210 align:middle line:84%
And maybe some of the debris
which is being thrown out

00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:52.410 align:middle line:84%
of the towers would have--
would have-- would have-- would

00:18:52.410 --> 00:18:57.050 align:middle line:84%
you say, compromised
Building Seven to an extent

00:18:57.050 --> 00:18:59.220 align:middle line:90%
that it would fall.

00:18:59.220 --> 00:19:01.190 align:middle line:84%
And-- and the first
response to that

00:19:01.190 --> 00:19:05.010 align:middle line:84%
would be would that be
reasonable to expect

00:19:05.010 --> 00:19:07.950 align:middle line:90%
with a seven hour delay?

00:19:07.950 --> 00:19:09.930 align:middle line:84%
Now, if Building
Seven had collapsed

00:19:09.930 --> 00:19:13.620 align:middle line:84%
due to shaking in
the ground, you would

00:19:13.620 --> 00:19:17.190 align:middle line:90%
expect an immediate action.

00:19:17.190 --> 00:19:20.680 align:middle line:84%
And-- but most
tellingly, actually,

00:19:20.680 --> 00:19:25.140 align:middle line:84%
is that the official report
on the Building Seven collapse

00:19:25.140 --> 00:19:29.000 align:middle line:84%
which came out of an
institution which is called

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:34.100 align:middle line:84%
the National Institute of
Standards and Technology,

00:19:34.100 --> 00:19:36.440 align:middle line:90%
abbreviated NIST.

00:19:36.440 --> 00:19:40.650 align:middle line:84%
This report from
NIST in that they--

00:19:40.650 --> 00:19:44.560 align:middle line:84%
they themselves
exclude what we call

00:19:44.560 --> 00:19:47.370 align:middle line:84%
mechanical damage
of Building Seven

00:19:47.370 --> 00:19:49.190 align:middle line:90%
as a cause for its collapse.

00:19:49.190 --> 00:19:51.610 align:middle line:84%
That means the
official account do

00:19:51.610 --> 00:19:56.300 align:middle line:84%
not-- the official
report does not

00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:59.370 align:middle line:84%
count on any physical
damage of Building 7.

00:19:59.370 --> 00:20:01.030 align:middle line:84%
So that's one thing
you could rule out.

00:20:01.030 --> 00:20:04.470 align:middle line:84%
There's been a lot of-- of
course many speculation.

00:20:04.470 --> 00:20:07.450 align:middle line:84%
Other-- another
bloom, as we call it,

00:20:07.450 --> 00:20:11.330 align:middle line:84%
which was launched
in intermediate years

00:20:11.330 --> 00:20:13.700 align:middle line:90%
was the diesel tanks.

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:17.580 align:middle line:84%
They had storage tanks for
the power emergency supplies.

00:20:17.580 --> 00:20:19.750 align:middle line:84%
There were diesel
tanks in the basement.

00:20:19.750 --> 00:20:22.240 align:middle line:84%
And somebody said, well,
the diesel tanks, they

00:20:22.240 --> 00:20:23.280 align:middle line:90%
fed the fires.

00:20:23.280 --> 00:20:24.620 align:middle line:90%
And that's what you had.

00:20:24.620 --> 00:20:26.810 align:middle line:90%
It was an inferno of fires.

00:20:26.810 --> 00:20:30.030 align:middle line:84%
NIST themselves rule
out this possibility

00:20:30.030 --> 00:20:33.250 align:middle line:90%
for different technical reasons.

00:20:33.250 --> 00:20:39.920 align:middle line:84%
So NIST claims that Building
7 fell due to ordinary office

00:20:39.920 --> 00:20:43.360 align:middle line:84%
fires, which there
were ordinary office--

00:20:43.360 --> 00:20:44.620 align:middle line:90%
office fires in the building.

00:20:44.620 --> 00:20:48.080 align:middle line:84%
But it was not a
roaring inferno.

00:20:48.080 --> 00:20:55.600 align:middle line:84%
There were random, small office
fires on six floors after two

00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:58.320 align:middle line:90%
o'clock in the afternoon.

00:20:58.320 --> 00:21:00.960 align:middle line:84%
And-- and the problem
with that explanation

00:21:00.960 --> 00:21:04.240 align:middle line:84%
is that it has-- there
are several problems.

00:21:04.240 --> 00:21:08.120 align:middle line:84%
But what should be
appreciated by everyone

00:21:08.120 --> 00:21:13.750 align:middle line:84%
is that it has never happened
before or after in history

00:21:13.750 --> 00:21:18.060 align:middle line:84%
that a steel frame high
riser-- and that is wha-- how--

00:21:18.060 --> 00:21:20.330 align:middle line:90%
what you call such a building.

00:21:20.330 --> 00:21:21.770 align:middle line:90%
We don't have them in Denmark.

00:21:21.770 --> 00:21:23.630 align:middle line:90%
We only use concrete.

00:21:23.630 --> 00:21:28.160 align:middle line:84%
But a steel frame high risesr--
that means a high riser built

00:21:28.160 --> 00:21:33.770 align:middle line:84%
around a steel skeleton--
buildings around this design

00:21:33.770 --> 00:21:39.515 align:middle line:84%
has never collapsed due to fire,
neither before or afterwards.

00:21:39.515 --> 00:21:41.740 align:middle line:84%
And of course, there have
been hundreds of fires

00:21:41.740 --> 00:21:43.330 align:middle line:90%
in buildings like that.

00:21:43.330 --> 00:21:47.250 align:middle line:84%
And what happens when you
have a fire in a high riser,

00:21:47.250 --> 00:21:50.070 align:middle line:84%
it means that the
firefighters, they come.

00:21:50.070 --> 00:21:51.620 align:middle line:90%
They go into the building.

00:21:51.620 --> 00:21:54.180 align:middle line:84%
The go to the floors
where the fires are.

00:21:54.180 --> 00:21:56.730 align:middle line:90%
And they put out the fires.

00:21:56.730 --> 00:22:00.510 align:middle line:84%
And firefighters,
they are brave.

00:22:00.510 --> 00:22:03.000 align:middle line:84%
They are courageous,
but they're not stupid.

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:06.390 align:middle line:90%
And they're not suicidal.

00:22:06.390 --> 00:22:09.400 align:middle line:84%
They know that
buildings like that

00:22:09.400 --> 00:22:12.670 align:middle line:90%
do not collapse due to fire.

00:22:12.670 --> 00:22:16.510 align:middle line:84%
And if, again, I may bring
in a scientific principle.

00:22:16.510 --> 00:22:18.870 align:middle line:84%
Each fire which there's
been in a steel frame high

00:22:18.870 --> 00:22:21.860 align:middle line:84%
riser you could,
maybe cynically,

00:22:21.860 --> 00:22:24.740 align:middle line:90%
consider as an experiment.

00:22:24.740 --> 00:22:27.590 align:middle line:84%
And after each fire,
you make the observation

00:22:27.590 --> 00:22:29.190 align:middle line:90%
the building did not collapse.

00:22:29.190 --> 00:22:32.230 align:middle line:84%
When you've see this
100, 200, 300 times,

00:22:32.230 --> 00:22:35.780 align:middle line:84%
you draw the conclusion the
steel frame high risers simply

00:22:35.780 --> 00:22:38.020 align:middle line:90%
do not collapse due to fire.

00:22:38.020 --> 00:22:39.760 align:middle line:90%
Period.

00:22:39.760 --> 00:22:42.415 align:middle line:84%
And still, NIST,
National Institute

00:22:42.415 --> 00:22:44.530 align:middle line:84%
of Standards and
Technology, claim

00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:48.440 align:middle line:84%
that this happened for the
first, single, and only

00:22:48.440 --> 00:22:50.380 align:middle line:90%
time in history on that day.

00:22:50.380 --> 00:22:56.680 align:middle line:84%
Already from there, you
know that their report is

00:22:56.680 --> 00:23:00.320 align:middle line:90%
a fraud, a scientific cover up.

00:23:00.320 --> 00:23:05.030 align:middle line:84%
But of course, the scientists
can go into the report which

00:23:05.030 --> 00:23:13.100 align:middle line:84%
is huge, and point to all of the
mistakes, all the errors, all

00:23:13.100 --> 00:23:18.350 align:middle line:84%
the deliberate omissions,
all the lies, and all

00:23:18.350 --> 00:23:21.980 align:middle line:84%
the dead meat, all
the hot air which

00:23:21.980 --> 00:23:25.420 align:middle line:84%
is in these reports
and point out all--

00:23:25.420 --> 00:23:29.520 align:middle line:84%
But this is an academic
pastime really.

00:23:29.520 --> 00:23:33.070 align:middle line:84%
Because basically,
in sum, we must

00:23:33.070 --> 00:23:36.750 align:middle line:84%
characterized the
official, technical reports

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:39.245 align:middle line:90%
as scientific fraud.

00:23:39.245 --> 00:23:40.500 align:middle line:90%
They're lying.

00:23:40.500 --> 00:23:43.710 align:middle line:84%
It is-- and this institute
I'm talking about

00:23:43.710 --> 00:23:47.300 align:middle line:84%
is not an independent
academic institution.

00:23:47.300 --> 00:23:51.680 align:middle line:84%
It is operating under
the Ministry of Commerce

00:23:51.680 --> 00:23:56.030 align:middle line:84%
in the United States and
the-- the-- the leadership

00:23:56.030 --> 00:24:00.810 align:middle line:84%
is appointed each time you
shift a new administration,

00:24:00.810 --> 00:24:02.000 align:middle line:90%
you have a new leadership.

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:07.730 align:middle line:84%
And particularly, the-- the--
