00:43:42.960 --> 00:43:48.060 align:middle line:84%
It is toxic and poisonous
for a variety of reasons.

00:43:48.060 --> 00:43:51.790 align:middle line:84%
First of all,
pulverized concrete is--

00:43:51.790 --> 00:43:54.361 align:middle line:84%
I have to use a technical
term now-- it's very--

00:43:54.361 --> 00:43:55.847 align:middle line:84%
LILOU MACE: Steel.
Pulverized steel.

00:43:55.847 --> 00:43:56.680 align:middle line:90%
NIELS HARRIT: No, no, no.

00:43:56.680 --> 00:43:58.680 align:middle line:84%
No, the steel was
not pulverized.

00:43:58.680 --> 00:43:59.430 align:middle line:90%
The concrete.

00:43:59.430 --> 00:44:03.650 align:middle line:84%
There were concrete slabs in
the building, namely the floors.

00:44:03.650 --> 00:44:04.720 align:middle line:90%
They were concrete.

00:44:04.720 --> 00:44:06.310 align:middle line:90%
They didn't carry anything.

00:44:06.310 --> 00:44:07.700 align:middle line:90%
But the floors were concrete.

00:44:07.700 --> 00:44:09.710 align:middle line:90%
It was completely pulverized.

00:44:09.710 --> 00:44:16.010 align:middle line:84%
Pulverized concrete-- it's
about 90,000 tons per tower.

00:44:16.010 --> 00:44:18.620 align:middle line:84%
Pulverized concrete
is very basic which

00:44:18.620 --> 00:44:22.120 align:middle line:84%
means that it actually burns the
lungs when you're breathing it.

00:44:22.120 --> 00:44:25.580 align:middle line:84%
There's a certain
threshold from-- from

00:44:25.580 --> 00:44:31.230 align:middle line:84%
above which you characterize
this kind of dust as unhealthy.

00:44:31.230 --> 00:44:34.320 align:middle line:84%
And below this it is
characterized as healthy.

00:44:34.320 --> 00:44:37.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, the agency's the
Environmental Protection

00:44:37.370 --> 00:44:42.620 align:middle line:84%
Agency, they deliberately
falsified the samples,

00:44:42.620 --> 00:44:45.300 align:middle line:84%
and actually took it
to get the measurement

00:44:45.300 --> 00:44:47.380 align:middle line:90%
below the threshold.

00:44:47.380 --> 00:44:50.170 align:middle line:84%
That means that they
lied about the health.

00:44:50.170 --> 00:44:52.760 align:middle line:84%
But this was a report which
came out later, of course,

00:44:52.760 --> 00:44:55.260 align:middle line:84%
in the days when
these things happen.

00:44:55.260 --> 00:44:57.540 align:middle line:84%
The Environmental
Protection Agency, they

00:44:57.540 --> 00:45:02.120 align:middle line:90%
launched 11 what would you say?

00:45:02.120 --> 00:45:07.420 align:middle line:84%
Decoration statements that the
air was healthy to breathe,

00:45:07.420 --> 00:45:10.650 align:middle line:84%
because they wanted
to reopen Wall Street.

00:45:10.650 --> 00:45:12.000 align:middle line:90%
That's one thing.

00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:19.930 align:middle line:84%
But another thing-- and-- and--
and-- other poisonous things

00:45:19.930 --> 00:45:27.020 align:middle line:84%
in the dust is pulverized
glass, glass fibers, asbestos.

00:45:27.020 --> 00:45:28.510 align:middle line:90%
I've seen it myself.

00:45:28.510 --> 00:45:30.090 align:middle line:90%
It's called chrysotile.

00:45:30.090 --> 00:45:34.370 align:middle line:84%
And you can see the
asbestos fibers in the dust.

00:45:34.370 --> 00:45:39.680 align:middle line:84%
Mercury, all other
metals, and, of course,

00:45:39.680 --> 00:45:41.960 align:middle line:90%
all other kind of chemicals.

00:45:41.960 --> 00:45:43.660 align:middle line:90%
It's simply not very healthy.

00:45:43.660 --> 00:45:45.290 align:middle line:84%
And these people
